data.title: Cut Nyak Dien
data.meta_description: CUT NYAK DIEN - Free download as Word Doc (.doc / .docx), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. Nyai Ahmad Dahlan was born in Yogyakarta to a religious family and was educated in religion from a young age. She supported her husband KH Ahmad Dahlan and his revolutionary Islamic teachings, helping establish Muhammadiyah organizations. Nyai Dahlan opened schools and literacy programs for women and established homes for the poor and orphaned. She promoted the spread of Islamic teachings and education for women throughout Java. Nyai Dahlan played a key role in establishing Aisyiyah, the women's wing of Muhammadiyah, and was considered a founder and guiding figure of the organization. She received the title of National Hero from the Indonesian government for her contributions to spreading Islam and educating women
